## The bands at a glance

| Band | Title milestone | The leap that gets you here | Primary focus | Roadmap |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **1500–1700** | strong club player | You **stop hanging pieces** and missing one-movers | Tactics volume, board vision, basic endgames, blunder-check | [→](09-Training-Plan/01-band-1500-1700.md) |
| **1700–1900** | Class A / expert track | You **calculate** instead of guessing; you understand structures | Calculation method, pawn structures, rook endgames, repertoire ideas | [→](09-Training-Plan/02-band-1700-1900.md) |
| **1900–2100** | Expert / Candidate Master | You **plan** and play **prophylactically** | Strategy depth, complex endgames, database-driven prep, model games | [→](09-Training-Plan/03-band-1900-2100.md) |
| **2100–2300** | FIDE Master / National Master | Your **calculation is deep and reliable**; few weaknesses remain | Visualization, refined repertoire + novelties, endgame mastery | [→](09-Training-Plan/04-band-2100-2300.md) |
| **2300–2500** | International Master → GM | You **prepare like a professional** and convert technically | Pro-level prep, engine/database depth, norms, fitness & psychology | [→](09-Training-Plan/05-band-2300-2500.md) |
| **2500–2800** | Grandmaster → world class | **Opening science, prodigious memory, peak calculation** | Novelties, deep theory, seconds, sports-science preparation | [→](09-Training-Plan/06-band-2500-2800.md) |

