## The non-negotiables (true at every rating)

1. **Tactics daily.** Pattern recognition is the engine of results below 2200 and never stops mattering. → [`03-Tactics/`](03-Tactics/)
2. **Analyze your own games — yourself, first.** The fastest feedback loop in chess. → [analysis method](01-Mindset-and-Study-Method/analyzing-your-own-games.md)
3. **Endgame technique.** Knowing the [opposition](05-Endgames/the-opposition.md), [triangulation](05-Endgames/triangulation.md), [Lucena & Philidor](05-Endgames/rook-endgames.md) turns half-points into points.
4. **A blunder-check before every move.** → [the thinking process](flowcharts/the-thinking-process.md).
5. **Deliberate practice over volume.** Work at the edge of your ability with feedback. → [deliberate practice](01-Mindset-and-Study-Method/deliberate-practice.md).

